# Contributing to the NowSecure Jenkins Plugin

First off, thank you for considering contributing! We're thrilled you're interested in helping us on our mission of saving the world from unsafe mobile apps.

## Code of Conduct

This project, like all Jenkins plugins, adheres to the [Jenkins Code of Conduct](https://www.jenkins.io/project/conduct/). By participating, you are expected to uphold this code. Please report unacceptable behavior to [jenkinsci-board@googlegroups.com].

## How Can I Contribute?

### GitHub Issues

Before submitting an issue of any kind, please look through the [existing issues](https://github.com/nowsecure/nowsecure-jenkins-ci-plugin/issues)
to see if a similar item has already been brought to our attention.

#### Bug Reports

This repository has issue templates to help you get started reporting incorrect behavior. 
To get started [create an issue](https://github.com/nowsecure/nowsecure-jenkins-ci-plugin/issues/new/choose) and be sure to choose the `Bug Report` template.
Please be sure to fill out all relevant information in your bug report.

#### Feature Requests

We welcome suggestions for new features or improvements to existing ones! 

To suggest an enhancement [create an issue](https://github.com/nowsecure/nowsecure-jenkins-ci-plugin/issues/new/choose) and be sure to choose the `Feature Request` template.
Please be sure to fill out all relevant information asked in the template.

### Your First Code Contribution

Not sure where to start? Look for issues tagged `good first issue` or `help wanted`. These are specifically set aside as good entry points into the codebase.

### Pull Requests

We use the "Fork and Pull" model for contributions.

1. **Fork** this repository to your own GitHub account, clone it down, and make your desired changes. 
For more information on how to work with forks, see [this GitHub page](https://docs.github.com/en/pull-requests/collaborating-with-pull-requests/working-with-forks/fork-a-repo) on forking a repo.
2. **Push** your branch to your fork: `git push origin feat/my-awesome-feature`
3. **Open a Pull Request** (PR) from your branch to the `main` branch of the upstream repository. 
For more information on creating pull requests from forks, check out the 
[this GitHub documentation](https://docs.github.com/en/pull-requests/collaborating-with-pull-requests/proposing-changes-to-your-work-with-pull-requests/creating-a-pull-request-from-a-fork)

